{"actual_usd":0.15623,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":197,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30655,"reply":"\"I wouldn't go that far.\" *I rub a thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and glance out across the bright square a moment, gathering the line before I lay it down.* \"Paul says Christ was buried, that He was raised on the third day, and then he starts naming witnesses. In a Jewish frame, 'buried' and 'raised' isn't naturally a ghost-story. It's a bodily claim.\"\n\n*I shift a little on the bench, the wood warm already where the sun has reached it.* \"Now, you're right that Paul doesn't stop and say the words empty tomb there. But omission isn't denial. A man can tell the heart of a thing without repeating every detail every time. If anything, 1 Corinthians 15 reads to me like he's handing on something his hearers already know, not inventing a thinner version.\"\n\n\"If you want, the sharper question is this: what kind of 'raised' do you think Paul meant there?\"","rolling_24h_usd":91.50145499999999,"run_id":"1a9424e5-beaa-480f-9673-bdc6bf0a170e"}
